time, and people who did see it but enjoyed it so much they want to watch it again.

00:10:03.828 --> 00:10:10.148
And if you grew up in the 1990s, as I did, you probably remember a series of films that went

00:10:10.148 --> 00:10:16.368
straight to video, that didn’t come out in the cinema, and were available to buy to watch at home.

00:10:17.338 --> 00:10:22.448
They were normally sequels of the Disney hit films, so you had Pocahontas II,

00:10:23.076 --> 00:10:28.746
The Return of Jafar, which was the sequel to Alladin, and around 25 others.

00:10:29.626 --> 00:10:33.146
